<% include header %>
<% include reusables/jumbotron_api %>
    <div class="row-fluid step-header span12">
        <div class="step-container">
	  <h3>Requests</h3>
	  <p>Requests represent design requests, e.g. the objects to be processed by our service. To start designing a hammerhead ribozyme, one needs to create a request, and supply it with the necessary parameters.</p>
	  <table class="table table-striped api-table">
	    <thead>
	      <tr>
		<th>Resource</th>
		<th>Description</th>
	      </tr>
	    </thead>
	    <tbody>
	      <tr>
		<td>POST /ribosoft/requests/</td>
		<td>Creates a new design request using the given design parameters, and returns 201 on success.<br/>
		  <br/>
		  <h4>Parameters</h4>
		  <ul>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>sequence : String</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">When provided, the sequence will be used as the target of the Hammerhead ribozyme.</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>accessionNumber: String</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">When provided, it will be used as the target of the Hammerhead ribozyme.<br/>Note that, when both the sequence and the accessionNumber are provided, they are validated to belong to the same organism.<br/> For a list of possible accession number values, have a look at the <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK25500/">NCBI database</a></p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>foldShape : String</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Describes the shape of the ribozyme.<br/> Possible values are: "Basic" and "Wishbone"</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>temperature : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the temperature of the target.<br/> Default value is 37&#8451;</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>naC : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the Na&#8314; concentration in the target environment.<br/> Default value is 0</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>mgC : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the Mg&#8314;&#8314; concentration in the target environment.<br/> Default value is 0</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>oligoC : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the concentration of oligos in the target environment.<br/> Default value is 0</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>cutsites : Array</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the list of cutsites that the ribozyme should target.</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>region : String</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the part of the RNA that will be targeted.<br/> This value is required when using the accession number.<br/> Possible values are: "5'", "ORF" and "3'"</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>left_arm_min : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the minimum length of the left arm strand. <br/>Default value is 3</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>left_arm_max : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the maximum length of the left arm strand. <br/>Default value is 8</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>right_arm_min : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the minimum length of the right arm strand. <br/>Default value is 3</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>right_arm_max : Integer</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the maximum length of the right arm strand. <br/>Default value is 8</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>promoter : Boolean</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents whether the T7 promoter should be used or not. <br/>Default value is false</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>env : Object</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Represents the target environment. <br/><em>env.type</em> can be either "vitro" or "vivo", for in-vitro and in-vivo respectively. <br/><em>env.target</em> is the target environment if in-vivo.</p></li>
		  </ul>
		  <br/>
		  <h4>Status code</h4>
		  <ul>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>201</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Returned when the request has been successfully created.<br/>The location header points to the location of the newly created request. Refer to the Return Value section for more details</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>400</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Returned when the request contains malformed, inconsistent or is missing data.</p></li>
		  </ul>
		</td>
	      </tr>
	      <tr>
		<td>GET /ribosoft/requests/:id</td>
		<td>Returns the information for request for which "id" is provided<br/><br/>
		  <h4>Parameters</h4>
		  <p>None</p>
		  <br/>
		  <h4>Status code</h4>
		  <ul>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>200</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Returned when the request has been found.<br/>Refer to the Return Value section for more details</p></li>
		    <li class="design-parameter"><em>404</em><br/><p class="parameter-desc">Returned when the request cannot be found.</p></li>
		  </ul>
		</td>
	      </tr>
	    </tbody>
	  </table>
        </div>
    </div>
